OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FThe death of a grandmother who was
OL,8,Fscratched by a dog in Morocco was not
OL,9,Fthe result of a delay in diagnosing
OL,10,Fher illness as rabies, an inquest jury
OL,11,Fhas found.
OL,13,FYvonne Ford, 59, from Barnsley, died
OL,14,Ffour months after she suffered a minor
OL,15,Fscratch when she startled a dog under
OL,16,Fher sun lounger on a beach during a
OL,17,Fholiday in February 2025.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FShe did not seek medical treatment at
OL,8,Fthe time but went to Barnsley Hospital
OL,9,Fin June of that year with a range of
OL,10,Fsymptoms including severe headaches,
OL,11,Fnausea, mobility issues and
OL,12,Fdisorientation.
OL,14,FMrs Ford was admitted a day later as
OL,15,Fher condition deteriorated, but
OL,16,Fdoctors struggled to work out what was
OL,17,Fwrong with her.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FHer inquest in Sheffield heard the
OL,8,F"rarity of the disease and unusual
OL,9,Fpresentation" caused problems with
OL,10,Fdiagnosis.
OL,12,FRabies was only identified after a
OL,13,Fpsychiatrist asked about Mrs Ford's
OL,14,Ftravel history when he was called in
OL,15,Fby medical colleagues who were
OL,16,Fconcerned about symptoms including
OL,17,Fhallucinations, disorientation and
OL,18,Fhigh levels of anxiety.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FShe was transferred to Sheffield's
OL,8,FRoyal Hallamshire Hospital where she
OL,9,Fdied on 11 June with her family around
OL,10,Fher wearing personal protective
OL,11,Fequipment (PPE), the inquest has heard.
OL,13,FIn a narrative conclusion on Thursday,
OL,14,Fa jury of eight men and two women
OL,15,Fconcluded: "The rarity of the disease
OL,16,Fand unusual presentation led to a
OL,17,Fdifficulty in reaching a diagnosis but
OL,18,Fthis did not affect the outcome."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FInfectious diseases expert Katharine
OL,8,FCartwright, from Sheffield Teaching
OL,9,FHospitals, told the jury during the
OL,10,Fthree-day inquest in Sheffield that
OL,11,Frabies is a virus that is 100% fatal
OL,12,Fonce the symptoms begin to show, but
OL,13,Fcan be prevented with a vaccine.
OL,15,FDr Cartwright said that rabies
OL,16,Fsymptoms typically begin within four
OL,17,Fweeks of exposure - but it can be up
OL,18,Fto three months and, in some cases, it
OL,19,Fcan take years.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FShe said it appeared that Mrs Ford
OL,8,Fbegan to exhibit symptoms at the very
OL,9,Fend of May and, therefore, there was
OL,10,Fnothing that could have been done at
OL,11,FBarnsley Hospital that would have
OL,12,Fsaved her.
OL,14,FDr Cartwright told the jury there have
OL,15,Fonly been 26 cases of rabies in the UK
OL,16,Fsince 1946.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FMrs Ford's daughter Robyn Thomson told
OL,8,Fthe inquest on Wednesday that it was
OL,9,Fvital the public are made aware that
OL,10,Fthey must seek urgent medical advice
OL,11,Fif they are scratched or bitten by an
OL,12,Fanimal abroad to prevent "another
OL,13,Ffamily from enduring this trauma, loss
OL,14,Fand devastation".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FShe said: "We are determined that
OL,8,FYvonne's death will not be without
OL,9,Fmeaning." Ms Thomson said Mrs Ford was
OL,10,Fa "loving, active and devoted family
OL,11,Fwoman" who was a "fantastic wife", a
OL,12,F"wonderful mother" and an "exceptional
OL,13,Fgrandmother" to her four grandchildren.
OL,15,FShe explained to the jury how family
OL,16,Fand staff had to wear gloves, masks,
OL,17,Fvisors and aprons when they were with
OL,18,Fher mother, from when she was admitted
OL,19,Fto Sheffield to when she died.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G8/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FMs Thomson told the inquest how the
OL,8,Ffamily were told "there is no possible
OL,9,Frecovery and that the only outcome
OL,10,Fwould be fatal" after rabies was
OL,11,Fconfirmed at the Royal Hallamshire.
OL,13,FShe said that "watching Yvonne
OL,14,Fdeteriorate so rapidly was extremely
OL,15,Ftraumatic" during her time at Barnsley
OL,16,FHospital.
OL,18,FMs Thomson told the jury of nine women
OL,19,Fand two men how they had to watch her
OL,20,Fdeteriorate "in real time without
OL,21,Fexplanation and with growing fear".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G9/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1772745123
OL,3,CDelay diagnosing rabies did not
OL,4,Ccontribute to grandmother's death,
OL,5,Cinquest finds
OL,7,FShe said the family had a number of
OL,8,Fconcerns about the basic care her
OL,9,Fmother received in Barnsley and added:
OL,10,F"We don't believe Yvonne was treated
OL,11,Fwith the level of dignity and respect
OL,12,Fshe deserved."
OL,14,FA spokesperson for Barnsley Hospital
OL,15,Fsaid: "Our thoughts are with Yvonne's
OL,16,Ffamily following the sad loss of a
OL,17,Floved family member in such unusual
OL,18,Fcircumstances."
OL,26,@wD@GOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G10/10
